Ad Text:
Making a difference isn’t just our purpose, it’s what motivates our people every day. For us, work is not about ticking a box. It’s about knowing that it matters. We make a meaningful difference every day by making it easier for our customers to focus on what matters in their lives. 

 If you enjoy owning foundational systems and making opinionated technical decisions that scale, this role is for you. As a Platform Engineer, you’ll design and operate a secure, resilient, cloud-native platform that underpins our financial services—from local development to mission-critical production.

 Here’s how you will make a difference in this role… 

You’ll be responsible for building, operating, and evolving our cloud-native platform to enable secure, scalable delivery across the business.

 At MMS clear expectations help our people Be the Difference.  Your key responsibilities in this role will include: 

Design, implement, and maintain Infrastructure as Code using Terraform

Build and operate CI/CD pipelines as code, enabling reliable, zero-downtime deployments

Apply platform engineering principles to improve consistency, automation, and developer experience at scale

Partner with application teams to uplift cloud security, pipeline quality, and delivery practices

Troubleshoot and resolve complex issues across cloud infrastructure, networking, and connectivity

Embed automation, security, and governance across the full development lifecycle

To be considered for this role you will have: 

Strong hands-on experience with Terraform and Infrastructure as Code

Experience building and operating cloud-native CI/CD pipelines

Solid understanding of platform engineering and DevOps practices in a regulated or enterprise environment

Ability to collaborate closely with development teams to enable secure, scalable delivery

Confidence working across cloud infrastructure, networking, and operational troubleshooting

A security-first mindset, with experience integrating governance and controls by design

 What we can offer you:

Novated leasing benefits and discounts

12 weeks paid parental leave and access to our Parents Portal

Comprehensive learning and development opportunities to support your career growth

Sonder digital wellbeing platform, providing personalised support 24/7, plus annual flu vaccinations

Default Income Protection Insurance reimbursed for members of the MMS Default Super Fund

Exempt Employee Share Plan

Embracing our value of Everyone Matters we hold a collective commitment to foster an environment where all differences are valued and respected. 

We encourage individuals from all backgrounds including Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples, those caring for someone or living with a disability, LGBTQIA+ and culturally diverse applicants to apply.

We embrace hybrid working and welcome conversations about flexibility. 

 Please note all successful candidates will undergo background checks (including criminal history and ASIC checks) and an NDIS Workers Screening Check if appropriate.  All information provided will be treated confidentially. 

 We acknowledge Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples as the Traditional Custodians of the lands where we live, learn and work.

 If you identify as a person living with disability and require adjustments to our recruitment process, please contact us at mmsgrouprecruitment@mmsg.com.au

LAF Technologies is a leading provider of Environmental Monitoring Solutions (EMS) to customers in the Pharmaceutical, Life Sciences, and Healthcare sectors. Australian-owned with offices in VIC, QLD, and TAS. We are now looking to expand our technical team in VIC. We pride ourselves on delivering exceptional solutions and support to our clients.




As a Systems Engineer, you will play a crucial role in designing, developing, installing, and supporting SCADA-based monitoring system projects.




Responsibilities:

• Creating EMS databases and transmission lists on Schneider GeoSCADA.

• Managing EMS project design and configuration of system software processes.

• Assist and ensure deliverables are achieved to client specifications.

• Proactively collaborate with the development of innovative solutions.

• Ensure projects are coordinated and managed efficiently through to commissioning.

• Act as the technical partner to our customers, being the BMS subject matter expert.

• Site management as required.

• Effective stakeholder management.




Requirements:

• An Engineering qualification (electrical or Industrial Automation).

• Solid SCADA programming (Schneider desirable, but others considered).

• Flexible approach to travel across ANZ with a valid Australian driver’s license.

• Proficient in the use of the Microsoft Office suite.

• Enthusiastic with a dedicated work ethic.

• Excellent problem-solving abilities.

• Effective communication and interpersonal skills.

• Residing in Australia, an Australian citizen or with a valid work permit.




Benefits:

• A competitive remuneration package, daily variety in work, and room for career development.

• Work within a friendly and collaborative workplace, where employees are valued and recognised.

• Supportive multicultural work environment and team-oriented culture.

In Brief:
This federal government department is looking to uplift and improve their data practices, processes and capabilities.  Data is a big part of what they do, and they're on a mission to improve the function.  To do this, they're looking for a Data Engineer who can help implement best practices and a mature approach to data across the organisation.
 
About the role:
Sitting in the data team, this role will be working with other Data Engineers and Data Scientists to bring the broader function on a journey towards best practices.  Right now the overall environment isn't mature.  They're looking towards Azure Fabric to trial the analytics capability and more broadly implement new tooling that will help with data management.  They're also leveraging Infrastructure as Code (Terraform), Graph Databases (Neo4J) to set the team up in a extensible way.
 
Data Engineer responsibilities:

Collaborate closely with business stakeholders to assess and grow their data maturity in accordance with platform standards, and data management frameworks and practices.
Design, build, test, deploy and maintain platform software and systems using a variety of technologies and disciplines.
Writing, testing and documenting code according to best standards and practices.
Contribute to platform and product initiatives.
Collaborating on solution designs and technical problems
Maintaining existing platform products and services, including bug fixes and "Business as Usual" feature enhancements.
About you:
With a strong understanding of Data Engineering best practices, you'll enjoy learning about new technologies and how these can be applied to real world problems.  You'll be hands on helping to set up and maintain data pipelines, build data models and work with the team to better leverage containerisation and cloud technologies.  You'll also be able to work with non-technical stakeholders and help business partners gain better insights from data.
 
Requirements:

A passion for data technologies, services and platforms.
Excellent software engineering skills, including experience delivering production-grade software in mainstream general-purpose languages such as Scala, Python, Rust, Go, .Net or Java.
Strong understanding of SQL and experience with relational database systems
A great communicator who loves collaborating with stakeholders and the tech community to build the best fit-for-purpose products.
Someone who looks at tricky situations through a solutions-focused lens.
Experience working with real-time and streaming data frameworks, such as Kafka or Azure Stream Analytics.
A background working with Spark or Hadoop is highly desirable.
For this role it is a requirement to have a current baseline or NV1 clearance.
This is a great opportunity to join a small team embarking on a major uplift in capability.  For further information please contact Reece at reece@arney.com.au.

Job Title: Cloud Solution Architect M365 Copilot & Agents
Ad Text:
Overview


With more than 45,000 employees and partners worldwide, the Customer Experience and Success (CE&S) organization is on a mission to empower customers to accelerate business value through differentiated customer experiences that leverage Microsoft’s products and services, ignited by our people and culture. We drive cross-company alignment and execution, ensuring that we consistently exceed customers’ expectations in every interaction, whether in-product, digital, or human-centered. CE&S is responsible for all up services across the company, including consulting, customer success, and support across Microsoft’s portfolio of solutions and products. Join CE&S and help us accelerate AI transformation for our customers and the world.

The Global Customer Success (GCS) organization, an organization within CE&S, is leading the effort to enable customer success on the Microsoft Cloud by harnessing leading, AI-powered capabilities and human expertise to deliver innovation solutions that accelerate business value, drive operational excellence and nurture long term loyalty.
We are looking for a Global Solution Architect (CSA), specializing in Copilot, who is passionate about driving our customers’ AI transformation on the Microsoft platform.  This role will be part of the Customer Success AI Business Solutions team and is designed to strategically engage in the execution of consumption within key accounts. This role will coach and collaborate with field roles and partners, executing programmatic actions that drive the consumption and AI transformation. This role will document and share best practices, ensure progress towards value realization goals, provide feedback to the Product Group, and facilitate knowledge transfer to field Customer Success Unit (CSU) teams. Additionally, the role involves partnering with field teams to identify key barriers to scaled success and driving resolution with engineering, product marketing, and sales teams. 
Step into the future of business transformation with our M365 Copilot and Agents incubation team! Here, you’ll be at the forefront of innovation, working as a Global Solution Architect to shape and validate the next generation of AI-powered business solutions. You’ll collaborate with engineering and business leaders to design, test, and refine cutting-edge use cases, leveraging real-world customer scenarios to drive product-market fit and create tangible learnings for the entire organization. Your ideas will directly influence the evolution of Microsoft 365 Copilot and Agents. 

What sets this role apart is its focus on incubation—where experimentation, rapid learning, and bold thinking are not just encouraged, but essential. You’ll join a select team tasked with validating early-stage solutions, capturing breakthrough use cases, and building the ROI methodology that will define the future of our platform. You’ll operate at the intersection of engineering and business, aligning with a global list of “frontier” customers and codifying best practices that will scale worldwide. If you thrive in ambiguity, love to create clarity from complexity, and want to be part of a team that’s setting the standard for how AI transforms work, we want you to help lead this journey! 

Microsoft’s mission is to empower every person and every organization on the planet to achieve more. As employees we come together with a growth mindset, innovate to empower others and collaborate to realize our shared goals. Each day we build on our values of respect, integrity, and accountability to create a culture of inclusion where everyone can thrive at work and beyond.

Responsibilities

Customer Satisfaction: Drive positive Customer Satisfaction, and become a trusted advisor to customers and partners, by leveraging AI fundamentals, Graph API, and Copilot for M365 expertise to enable defined Customer Success Plan outcomes. You will actively listen and respectfully challenge to drive the best outcomes.

Customer/Partner Insights: Provide feedback & insights from customers/partners back to the relevant MS teams including Product Groups, to enable continuous improvement. 

Accelerate Value Realization: Actively engage with business and technical decision makers to drive intent, enablement and usage of Copilot for M365, securing long-term customer renewal. Galvanize technical and sales experts around additional identified opportunities to develop customer specific roadmaps that drive further growth & business value realization.

Usage (Cloud & Support) Growth: Develop opportunities to drive Customer Success business results by working with business & technical decision makers to ensure they understand Microsoft's M365 Copilot value proposition. Lead architecture design sessions on M365 Copilot, address customer questions and provide best practices for activating solution within customer environment. 

Identify resolutions to issues blocking the go-live of customer success projects by leveraging deep knowledge of M365 Copilot for M365 technical subject matter expertise. Lead business & technical conversations with customers to drive value from their MS investments. Deliver all work according to MS best practices & policies and using repeatable IP. 

Learn It All: Demonstrate Self Learner mindset through continuous alignment of individual skilling to team/area demands and Customer Success goals

Accelerate Customer Outcomes: Engage in relevant communities to share expertise, contribute to IP creation, prioritize IP re-sure, and learn from others to help accelerate your customers’ transformation journey.

Qualifications

Required Qualifications:

•    Bachelor's degree in computer science, Information Technology, Engineering, Business, or related field AND 4+ years' experience in cloud/infrastructure technologies, information technology (IT) consulting/support, systems administration, network operations, software development/support, technology solutions, practice development, architecture, and/or consulting.

o    OR equivalent experience

Agentic AI Experience with Microsoft/Google/Amazon/Open AI/Any 3rd party

Hands on Agents/Chat bot building skills on Microsoft copilot studio/Azure foundry/3rd party platforms

D365 Experience

Consultative sales experience

Preferred Qualifications

Bachelors Degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, Engineering, Business, or related field AND 8+ years experience in cloud/infrastructure technologies, information technology (IT) consulting/support, systems administration, network operations, software development/support, technology solutions, practice development, architecture, and/or consulting

OR Masters Degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, Engineering, Business, or related field AND 6+ years experience in cloud/infrastructure technologies, technology solutions, practice development, architecture, and/or consulting

OR equivalent experience

4+ years experience working in a customer-facing role (e.g., internal and/or external).

4+ years experience working on technical projects.

Technical Certification in Cloud (e.g., Azure, Amazon Web Services, Google, security certifications

Change management certifications such as Prosci Certified Advanced Change Practitioner (PCACP) 

This position will be open for a minimum of 5 days, with applications accepted on an ongoing basis until the position is filled.

Microsoft is an equal opportunity employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to age, ancestry, citizenship, color, family or medical care leave, gender identity or expression, genetic information, immigration status, marital status, medical condition, national origin, physical or mental disability, political affiliation, protected veteran or military status, race, ethnicity, religion, sex (including pregnancy), sexual orientation, or any other characteristic protected by applicable local laws, regulations and ordinances. If you need assistance with religious accommodations and/or a reasonable accommodation due to a disability during the application process, read more about requesting accommodations.

The role

Are you passionate about data integrity and seamless system transitions? In this role, you’ll play a critical part in migrating data into Oracle Cloud ERP, ensuring accuracy, security, and performance every step of the way. You’ll work with cutting-edge tools like PL/SQL, Oracle Autonomous Database, and FBDI templates to extract, transform, and load data efficiently.

You’ll collaborate closely with business analysts and stakeholders, tackle complex data challenges, and help deliver a smooth migration that supports our business transformation. If you thrive on problem-solving and precision, this is your opportunity to make a real impact.

This is a 12-month contract, with potential to extend.

What you'll do
Design, develop, and test PL/SQL routines for ETL processes to move data efficiently and securely.
Analyse source and target data models, perform data mapping, and resolve data quality issues through cleansing and enrichment.
Validate and reconcile data between source and target systems.
Collaborate with business analysts, developers, and stakeholders to define requirements and resolve data challenges.
Support SIT and UAT phases, ensuring data integrity checks are completed.
Create technical documentation, data flow diagrams, and migration reports.
Participate in team meetings and workshops to drive successful outcomes.
What you'll bring
5+ years’ experience in data migration, particularly with Oracle databases and ERP environments.
Advanced Oracle PL/SQL skills and strong ETL process knowledge.
Familiarity with Oracle Finance and Procurement data sets.
Experience with Oracle FBDI templates.
Strong analytical and problem-solving skills with attention to detail.
Why Join Us?

At Kinetic, we’re committed to improving the livelihoods of the communities we serve. We offer:

A collaborative and supportive team environment.
Opportunities to work on cutting-edge Oracle Cloud ERP projects.
A culture that prioritises safety, wellbeing, and continuous improvement.

Salary: No contractor fees / two pay runs per week
Ad Text:
Cloud Identity Architect

Contract to 18/09/2026 | Carseldine | Hybrid working

We are partnering with a leading Queensland Government client to recruit an experienced Cloud Identity Architect. In this role, you will be designing, enhancing, and governing IAM capabilities—including identity lifecycle management, access controls, authentication, and authorisation frameworks—to ensure secure and efficient access to systems and applications.

Key Requirements:

Work across multiple architectural domains such as business, information, application, technology, and information security.

Review of external supplier provided enterprise architecture artefacts (ICT strategies, position papers and direction statements).

Contribute to configurations of cloud-based systems and applications.

Develop cloud adoption plans and architectural artefacts for public, private, or hybrid cloud environments (for example conceptual and logical solution designs, data integration and information models).

Develop and maintain effective relationships with key internal and external stakeholders, such as, ITB Subject Matter Experts (SME's), business SMEs, Queensland Government Chief Information Office (QGCIO), and the ICT industry.

Define and enforce security standards, ensuring infrastructure meets regulatory requirements.

Work with developers, security, and other IT teams to integrate cloud services seamlessly. Serve as the primary liaison between technical staff and business stakeholders, translating complex technical requirements into actionable strategies.

What We’re Looking For

Proven experience in an Architect or Solution Consultant role, with a superior ability to decompose complex technical pictorials and data workflows.

Broad understanding of the IAM cybersecurity landscape, including identity stores, modern authentication, and Zero Trust principles.

Familiarity with:

Microsoft Entra ID, Azure IAM, and Active Directory.

Microsoft Security Services (Defender for Identity, AIP, MCAS) and MS Intune.

Scripting languages and automation authoring controls.

Proficiency in Visio and PPTX to produce high-quality architectural diagrams and pictorials.

Ability to analyse system attribute extracts to support decision-making for integration and orchestration changes.

A background spanning both public and private sectors with experience in technical operations or large-scale ICT projects.

Why apply through Lime Recruitment?

Enjoy two pay runs per week without contractor fees. As a Queensland-owned agency, we offer personalised service and are a Tier 1 supplier to the Queensland Government. Awarded Australia’s top-performing small agency in 2021 and 2022, with a finalist spot in 2023. Partner with Lime for genuine, experienced, friendly recruiters dedicated to securing the best opportunities for you. Apply now or contact Kate Gear on 0477 624 569 or kate@limejobs.com.au to find out more!

Data and Integrations Manager

Type: Full-time
Location: Sydney, Melbourne or Brisbane
Reports to: Head of Application Engineering

As the Data and Integrations Manager at I-MED Radiology, you'll play a pivotal role in shaping and delivering the technology that underpins critical healthcare services across Australia and New Zealand. You'll lead the design and implementation of HL7-based integrations, ensuring secure, reliable, and high-quality solutions for both our business and our clients.

This role will see you establish and mature I-MED's data capability, working closely with business leaders, IT leadership, and enterprise architects to define the future state of data engineering, and to build the teams, systems, and structures required to achieve it.

As an inspiring people leader, you are an exceptional communicator and influencer who drives operational excellence through empowerment, accountability, and collaboration. You're equally comfortable in strategic conversations or diving into the technical detail when it matters.

Who we are

I-MED Radiology Network is Australia and New Zealand's largest diagnostic imaging network, offering medical imaging and radiology services including x-ray, PET, CT, MRI, Nuclear Medicine, Ultrasound, Mammography and interventional procedures.

At I-MED Radiology Network there is a strong belief that we can be the most respected and trusted medical imaging specialists in the world. That's our vision, underpinned by our purpose - to help save lives and reduce uncertainty. We strive to be the provider of choice, providing answers to health questions and delivering high quality care and service to our patients and referrers, every time.

Benefits

We offer a wide range of exclusive benefits - including health insurance discounts, salary packaging, Fitness Passport access, lifestyle perks through Perkbox, discounter and bulk billed I-MED services for you and your family as well as comprehensive wellbeing support.

What you'll do


Lead the design, development, and maintenance of hospital integration solutions
Oversee the delivery of integration and data solutions aligned with architectural strategies and standards
Define and implement patterns, schemas, and storage solutions that support scalable data and integration frameworks
Partner with business and IT stakeholders to evolve and continuously improve data and integration architecture
Manage vendor relationships to ensure optimal service delivery and performance
Oversee release management, testing, and system maintenance activities
Collaborate with Clinic Leaders and business stakeholders to support and drive adoption of IT solutions
Troubleshoot and resolve issues in line with company ITSM standards for service requests, incidents, problems, and change management
Work closely with infrastructure and operations teams to automate monitoring, response, and recovery processes
Participate in an on-call roster providing 24/7 support for critical incidents

What you've done


Bachelor's degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, or a related discipline
Experience in healthcare IT, focusing on integrations and/or data management
Proven expertise in HL7 and DICOM standards and protocols
Strong understanding of data management principles, including data modelling, ETL, and data quality
Experience working with RIS and PACS applications
Demonstrated leadership and team management skills
Excellent communication and stakeholder engagement abilities

Shape the future of healthcare data and integration at Australia's leading radiology network.

Company: Talent – Specialists in tech, transformation & beyond

Position Brief - Transport Systems Analyst

About the team

The Transport Systems Intelligence (TSI) team is a fun, dynamic team within the Transport Operations Business Unit. Our vision is to foster a safer transport environment by optimising operational efficiency, empowering informed decisions for network operators and establishing the groundwork for transport technology advancements.

About the role

The Transport Network Analyst will provide support to the Principal Transport Network Analyst in undertaking transport and traffic analysis for the Gold Coast transport system, with a focus on optimising the safety and efficiency of the road network.

This includes:

· Develop route and corridor traffic planning studies to maximise the operational efficiency of the Gold Coast road network.

· Assist in monitoring and reporting on the performance of strategic corridors and roads of significance.

· Provide technical advice to support traffic engineering and planning initiatives.

· Preparation of traffic assessments.

· Assist in identifying network pinch points and network optimisation treatments.

· Coordinate and liaise with internal stakeholders and external consultants to deliver efficient outcomes.

We’re looking for people who have:

Bachelor’s degree relevant to the position (e.g. engineering, planning) or equivalent industry experience.

· Demonstrated experience as a traffic professional.

· Experience with using SIDRA, and other microsimulation software.

· Knowledge of modern traffic modelling methodologies and practices.

· Unrestricted ‘C’ Class Drivers Licence.

· You thrive on applying innovative approaches to programs and problem solving.

· You foster positive relationships with stakeholders.

· You contribute to supporting outcomes that help build a connected and intelligent transport network for the Gold Coast.

· You have excellent verbal, written and interpersonal communication skills; with experience in developing grant submissions, education awareness campaigns and writing reports.

· You work productively in a team environment and foster positive relationships with other team members.

About the role
The Data Scientist, part of the Data Science Chapter within Product & Commercial, plays a crucial role in driving AGL's profitability. They build and maintain advanced data models, analyse complex datasets, and develop predictive models to solve business problems and uncover growth opportunities.

Reporting functionally to the GM of Product & Commercial and the Data Science chapter lead, Data Scientists are embedded in cross-functional teams to support business objectives. They maintain strong ties with the Data Science Chapter for capability development, knowledge sharing, and aligning on data practices, while being accountable for upholding data standards and achieving business goals.

What you'll be doing:

Build and iterate machine learning models to tackle business challenges like customer segmentation and marketing optimization.
Enhance model performance through feature engineering, hyperparameter tuning, and ensemble methods.
Conduct experiments to test hypotheses and derive actionable insights from data.
Create compelling visualizations to effectively communicate complex insights to stakeholders.
Identify new applications for data science to generate refined insights.
Stay updated on industry trends and emerging technologies to drive innovation

About you:

Previous demonstrated experience in customer segmentation and predictive behaviour modelling.
Strong analytical skills, with experience in applying statistical techniques to solve business problems.
Proficient in developing and implementing predictive models, segmentation models, and other statistical models using tools such as R, Python, or SAS (Python preferred).
Basic SQL skills and understanding of version control systems (ie. Git repository)
Experience in using data visualization tools such as Tableau or Power BI to effectively communicate complex findings to both technical and non-technical stakeholders.
Knowledge of the energy industry, including familiarity with energy consumption patterns, regulatory frameworks, and industry-specific challenges. - preferred - not essential.

Ad Text:
Great opportunity for an Automation Engineer with up to 0 - 2 years experience.
Ideal for a Graduate or a Graduate with 1-2 year experience.
Due to internal promotion, an excellent position has become available working with a renowned Global Pharmaceutical Manufacturer based in the South Eastern suburbs near Clayton.
Apply now for this rare opportunity! Here are the details below:

Reporting to the Automation Manager, the Automation Engineer position is a subject matter expert for automation, electrical and control systems.

The focus of this role is to ensure reliability, robustness, throughput and security of new and existing equipment/systems. This is done by completing or contributing towards projects and implementing other minor modifications/changes as required. This role contributes to the overall plan towards Industry 4.0 and the integration of other business systems such as SAP with factory automation.

Additionally, this position supports the factory with day to day issues that arise involving the automation and electrical systems including PLC/SCADA and other OT software.

Day to day responsibilities include:

Project support/system design

·       Implement minor projects and participate as a team member for larger projects.

·       Implement PLC hardware and software changes. Make changes to HMIs/SCADAs and other OT systems as required

·       Undertake electrical designs including cabinet layouts

·       Produce electrical drawings for modifications

·       Prepare design specifications and work packages Technicians and Contractors

·       Develop User Requirement Specifications (URS) and Qualification documents (IQ/OQ/PQ)

·       Complete commissioning and validation/qualification where required

·       Design, program and document small automation projects autonomously

·       Coordinate contractors and tradespeople to perform automation works including both software and hardware

Day to day support

Provide technical support to resolve day to day issues on the PLC network, servers and automation software

·       Support Technicians with troubleshooting issues related to automation

·       Investigate deviation incidents and implement corrective actions

·       Become subject matter expert for automation system software (Iltis, 3WS, C# applications)

·       Administer and manage applications on the factory network such as 3WS and user management on Active Directory

·       Update and upgrade automation and Windows operating systems to ensure that cyber security risks are minimised

·       Provide support to production on new equipment

Documentation

Ensure that adequate and accurate documentation is generated and stored with a high attention to detail

·       Manage and complete electrical drawing updates

·       Perform critical spares assessments

·       Ensure software backups are correctly stored in the backups repository

·       Ensure that appropriate system documentation is filed in the Engineering DMS folders

·       Ensure that safety design, validation and testing documentation is filed in the Engineering DMS folders

·       Create Isolation Procedures where required

·       Complete Change Management documentation

GxP

Ensure the principles of GxP are observed through all activities

·       Maintain an understanding of the principles of GxP

·       Ensure routine tasks are covered by approved Standard Operating Procedures (SOPs)

·       Ensure relevant changes are covered by Change Control Procedures (CCPs) with appropriate authorisation and testing

Work related requirements/selection criteria:

Education and qualifications required:

Bachelor Engineering (Electrical, Mechatronics or Software)

Experience required:

Experience in a manufacturing environment or as a system integrator (pharmaceutical, cosmetics, food or chemical industries would be relevant) is desirable

Skills required:

·       Strong fault finding and problem solving abilities

·       Ability to work effectively in a team or individually

·       High attention to detail

·       Good communication skills, both written and oral

·       Experience programming, maintaining and commissioning PLC hardware and software (Siemens, Allen-Bradley etc.)

·       Experience configuring, maintaining and commissioning SCADA/Historian/OPC software packages

·       Programming experience (.NET C#, ladder (Rockwell, Siemens))

·       Understanding of industrial Ethernet networks (VLANs, subnets)

·       Experience designing safety systems in accordance with AS/NZS 4024

·       Electrical drawing design and updating (AutoCAD or similar)

·       GAMP5 experience (desirable)

Must have PR, AU or NZ Citizenship to be eligible to apply.

Ad Text:
Job Title: Mid-Level AI Analyst - Governance & Ethics
Location: Sydney CBD
Employment Type: Full-time / long term contract opportunity
Salary: Negotiable contract rate on offer

About the Role

We are seeking a hands-on Mid-Level AI Analyst, and this role is ideal for someone passionate about AI governance, ethics, and responsible AI frameworks, who enjoys translating complex technical risks into practical advice and solutions.
You will work across government, enterprise, and technical teams to assess AI initiatives, monitor compliance, and support the implementation of robust governance processes. This is not a policy-making role , it's analytical, advisory, and deeply hands-on, offering exposure to cutting-edge AI projects in a high-impact environment.

Key Responsibilities

Conduct AI governance and ethics assessments across projects, identifying potential risks, bias, fairness, and compliance issues.
Support implementation of AI governance frameworks, approval gates, and monitoring processes.
Collaborate with policy, IT, legal, privacy, and business teams to provide clear, actionable guidance on AI projects.
Document and report findings, including risk assessments, dashboards, and governance committee materials.
Stay up to date with AI regulatory requirements, privacy laws, and ethical AI principles, ensuring projects align with best practice.
Assist in embedding responsible AI practices and frameworks.


Skills & Experience
Essential:

Hands-on experience in AI governance, ethics, and responsible AI frameworks.
Understanding of ethical AI principles: bias/fairness, & transparency.
Experience assessing AI projects for compliance, risk, and governance concerns.
Strong analytical skills and ability to review data sets, model outputs, or AI tools.
Experience with ServiceNow or similar governance/tracking tools.
Excellent communication skills to translate technical risks into clear advice for senior management.


Desirable / Nice-to-Have:

Background in government/public sector, consulting, finance, regulated industries, academia, or tech companies with AI governance exposure.
Knowledge of AI regulatory requirements, PIAs, or model risk frameworks.
Experience supporting governance committees, dashboards, and reporting frameworks.

"If AI governance and ethics excite you, we want to hear from you!"
